The orbital period of the #FalconHeavy / Tesla is ~2.4 years, meaning that every 2.4 years it is back near Earth's orbit (but not necessarily close to Earth). In 12 years from now, in February 2030, it should be relatively close to Earth again.

So, now it is in a heliocentric orbit with aphelion at 2.61 AU, the #FalconHeavy /Tesla moves at an orbital speed of 36.3 km/s near perihelion (near earth orbit). Near aphelion, in the asteroid belt, it moves with 13.6 km/s. pic.twitter.com/pyo3u1P6kl
